Anglo American, New Europe, Sea Kay: South African Equity Market Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a   a n d   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 
2011-02-11T05:51:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-10/anglo-american-new-europe-sea-kay-s-african-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South Africa .
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index fell the
most since Jan. 28, dropping 268.08, or 0.8 percent, to
32,409.48 at the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.    Anglo American Plc  (AGL SJ): De Beers, the world’s biggest
diamond company, releases annual results and sales after 9 a.m.
local time. De Beers is owned by Anglo, the Oppenheimer family
and Botswana’s government. Shares in Anglo slipped 1.6 percent
to 381.79 rand.    Blue Financial Services Ltd . (BFS SJ): The provider of
unsecured loans said it plans to sell 50 million rand ($6.9
million) worth of shares to an empowerment trust. The stock was
unchanged at 27 cents.    Kumba Iron Ore Ltd . (KIO SJ): The Department of Mineral
Resources agreed to delay the award of a partial mining right
over its Sishen mine to Imperial Crown Trading until Kumba’s
legal challenge to an initial prospecting right is heard,
Business Day said, citing Chief Financial Officer Vincent Uren.
Shares in Kumba, a unit of Anglo American, fell 3.16 rand, or
0.7 percent, to 460.50 rand.  New Europe Property Investments Plc (NEP SJ): The property
investment company said earnings for the year through December
rose 12 percent to 17.61 euro cents ($0.25) per share. Shares in
New Europe were unchanged at 30.20 rand.  Sasol Ltd. (SOL SJ): The world’s biggest maker of motor
fuel from coal had its outlook revised by  Standard & Poor’s  to
“stable” from “negative.” Sasol gained 3.64 rand, or 1
percent, to 369.81 rand.    Sea Kay Holdings Ltd . (SKY SJ): The builder of low-cost
houses said it had fulfilled its financial commitments to the
state-owned National Housing Finance Corp. to repay its debt and
avoid liquidation. Sea Kay closed unchanged at 15 cents.    Anglo American Plc  (AAUKY US) rose 0.5 percent to $26.55.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) fell 1.6 percent to $44.73. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) slipped 0.8 percent to $80.05. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) lost 0.6 percent to $4.64. Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI
US) declined 1.9 percent to $15.98. Harmony Gold Mining Co. (HMY
US) slid 1.7 percent to $10.77. Impala Platinum Holdings (IMPUY
US) gained 0.2 percent to $29.16. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US) slid 1.7
percent to $5.13.  Sasol Ltd . (SSL US) rose 1 percent to $51.21.  To contact the reporters on this story:
